GetAlgoName

public java.lang.String GetAlgoName()
This returns the one word name of the algorithm. This algorithm name may be followed by a separator slash and an input generator name if there exist more than one input generator for this particular algorithm. If that is the case, this function will return that full string. If you need just the algo name with out the input generator, use the utility method GetAlgoNameMinusIngen Two different algorithms should not have the same name.

GetAlgoNameMinusIngen

public static java.lang.String GetAlgoNameMinusIngen(java.lang.String theFullName)
Given the full AlgoName as returned by GetAlgoName, this method return only that portion of the algo name up to but not including the separator and ingen name

SetDynamicStatus

public void SetDynamicStatus(java.lang.String Status)
This allows the client to set all the pertinant information about the algorithm. "static" means the script is fixed, so the algorithm cannot share data/has no friends. "new_data_only" means that a script file is generated for the algorithm each time, but new data must always be generated for it. "dynamic" means that the algorithm has a script generated for it and it may share its data with itself and the algorithms in its friend vector. "dynamic-ingen" means the same as dynamic, but if the algorithm requires an input generator the server needs to send it only when new data when the user requests new data be generated.

GetDynamicStatus

public boolean GetDynamicStatus()
This returns true, if the server needs to generate a script file. false, if the script is fixed.

GetAlwaysNeedsInputGenerator

public boolean GetAlwaysNeedsInputGenerator()
This returns true, if the server always needs to send its input generator. false, if the input generator is only neccessary with new data.

SetVisualizerType

This allows the client to set a one word string identifying the visualizer that can run this algorithm's script file. i.e. Samba, Gaigs, or JavaApp
